introduction: This is one way to get ahead in life.

vocabulary.definition: a chronic disorder characterized by dependence on alcohol consumption
vocabulary.example: Her family intervened when they realized her alcoholism was spiraling out of control.

vocabulary.definition: the quality of being committed to a task or purpose
vocabulary.example: His dedication to his craft earned him the respect of his peers.

vocabulary.definition: spread or passed from place to place
vocabulary.example: Rumors about the new product features circulated among the employees.

vocabulary.definition: the act of acquiring or gaining possession of something
vocabulary.example: The company announced the acquisition of a smaller competitor.

vocabulary.definition: an object made by a human being, typically of cultural or historical interest
vocabulary.example: Archaeologists uncovered ancient artifacts in the tomb.

vocabulary.definition: a base or support on which something stands
vocabulary.example: The statue was placed on a marble pedestal in the center of the square.
